d":"<p>Taking a cursory look, it seems like PathPlanner doesn’t touch your gyro at all, so you will have to do that manually. Something along the lines of grabbing the initial heading from the PathPlanner path and applying it to your gyro upon initialization.</p>","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"posts_count":9,"updated_at":"2025-03-13T04:39:20.262Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":55,"readers_count":54,"score":16.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":495413,"topic_slug":"pathplanner-heading-issue","display_username":"Dylan Powers","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":42126,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":""},"post_url":"/t/pathplanner-heading-issue/495413/2","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3555939,"name":"","username":"RoyalKnight","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/r/ce7236/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-03-13T09:48:36.089Z","cooked":"<p>Thank you so much! I kind of realized this as well but I’m not really sure if that’s what I should do as in hard coding it… Is that what you guys do?</p>","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"posts_count":9,"updated_at":"2025-03-13T09:51:50.891Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":2,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":40,"readers_count":39,"score":18.0,"yours":false,"topic_id"