<p>My team does the following:</p>
<pre data-code-wrap="java"><code class="lang-java">double degreeOffset = DriverStation.getAlliance().get().equals(Alliance.Red) ? 180 : 0;
mSwerveSubsystem.resetHeading(auto.getStartingPose().getRotation().getDegrees() + degreeOffset);
</code></pre>
<p>It sets the gyro’s value based on the starting angle of the autonomous, you need to note that you MUST do it before you reset the odemeter because if your first reset the odemeter than the gyro it will cause your robot to think that its facing the wrong way and drive backwards (if you want i can explain why).<br>
If you are wandering why the offset - see that when you are in the red alliance your robot is facing the drivers so it’s at 180 degrees, but because path planner’s angles are relative to the blue side it says that you are at 0 degrees, i.e. there is a 180 degree offset when you are at the red alliance.</p>","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"posts_count":9,"updated_at":"2025-03-13T10:16:27.045Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":3,"quote_count":1,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":34,"readers_count":33,"score":11.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":495413,"topic_slug":"pathplanner-heading-issue","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":71857,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Vigilante"},"post_url":"/t/pathplanner-heading-issue/495413/4","custom_user_title":"Vigilante","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3555951,"name":"","username":"RoyalKnight","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/r/ce7236/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-03-13T10:21:33.285Z","cooked":"<p>I am facing the alliance wall in both the red and blue alliance autos, so I would just keep 180 both times I think?</p>
<p>Thank you so much for the help Batman <img src="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/images/emoji/google/pray.png?v=12" title=":pray:" class="emoji" alt=":pray:" loading="lazy" width="20" height="20"></p>","post_number":5,"post_type":1,"posts_count":9,"updated_at":"2025-03-13T10:21:33.285Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":4,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":24,"readers_count":23,"score":9.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":495413,"topic_slug":"pathplanner-heading-issue","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":71857,"username":"TheBatman","name":"","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/thebatman/{size}/255139_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":65426,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/pathplanner-heading-issue/495413/5","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3555952,"name":"","username":"TheBatman","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/thebatman/{size}/255139_2.png","created_at":"2025-03-13T10:27:30.425Z","cooked":"<p>I dont think so, see that in your blue auto that start position already has start angle of 180 so the offset should be 0 and that would result with your gyro reporting 180 as it should,<br>
and in the red alliance the path planner reports a start angle of 0 so the offset of 180 would result in the gyro reporting 180 degrees as it should.<br>
Happy to help <img src="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/images/emoji/google/bat.png?v=12" title=":bat:" class="emoji" alt=":bat:" loading="lazy" width="20" height="20"> <img src="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/images/emoji/google/superhero.png?v=12" title=":superhero:" class="emoji" alt=":superhero:" loading="lazy" width="20" height="20"></p>","post_number":6,"post_type":1,"posts_count":9,"updated_at":"2025-03-13T10:27:30.425Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":5,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":25,"readers_count":24,"score":10.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":495413,"topic_slug":"pathplanner-heading-issue","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":65426,"username":"RoyalKnight","name":"","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/r/ce7236/{size}.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":71857,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Vigilante"},"post_url":"/t/pathplanner-heading-issue/495413/6","custom_user_title":"Vigilante","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3555954,"name":"","username":"RoyalKnight","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/r/ce7236/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-03-13T10:36:03.044Z","cooked":"<p>Gotcha, I will try this and see… Where do you put this code? In the swerve subsystem? Robot. Java?</p>","post_number":7,"post_type":1,"posts_count":9,"updated_at":"2025-03-13T10:36:03.044Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":6,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":20,"readers_count":19,"score":14.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":495413,"topic_slug":"pathplanner-heading-issue","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":71857,"username":"TheBatman","name":"","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/thebatman/{size}/255139_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":65426,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/pathplanner-heading-issue/495413/7","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3555961,"name":"","username":"TheBatman","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/thebatman/{size}/255139_2.png","created_at":"2025-03-13T10:52:20.617Z","cooked":"<p>We put it in the getAutonomousCommand, it does mean that it’s a little problematic if you want to practice tele-op, in that case you can always quickly reset the heading in the code (or in the tele-op if you have a button for it).<br>
Here is the code segment where we put it:</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">public Command getAutonomousCommand() {
    PathPlannerAuto auto = (PathPlannerAuto)AutoBuilder.buildAuto(...);

    double degreeOffset = DriverStation.getAlliance().get().equals(Alliance.Red) ? 180 : 0;
    mSwerveSubsystem.resetHeading(auto.getStartingPose().getRotation().getDegrees() + degreeOffset);
    mSwerveSubsystem.resetPose(auto.getStartingPose());
    return auto;
}
</code></pre>","post_number":8,"post_type":1,"posts_count":9,"updated_at":"2025-03-13T10:52:20.617Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":7,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":20,"readers_count":19,"score":9.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":495413,"topic_slug":"pathplanner-heading-issue","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":65426,"username":"RoyalKnight","name":"","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/r/ce7236/{size}.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":71857,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Vigilante"},"post_url":"/t/pathplanner-heading-issue/495413/8","custom_user_title":"Vigilante","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3555965,"name":"","username":"RoyalKnight","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/r/ce7236/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-03-13T11:01:38.857Z","cooked":"<p>Perfect!! I will try this in a few hours before we leave and lyk the results!</p>","post_number":9,"post_type":1,"posts_count":9,"updated_at":"2025-03-13T11:01:38.857Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":8,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":18,"readers_count":17,"score":18.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":495413,"topic_slug":"pathplanner-heading-issue","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_i